Findings: The cardiac, hilar, and mediastinal contours are normal. The pulmonary vascularity is normal. Mild elevation of the right hemidiaphragm is unchanged with mild tenting of the diaphragm suggestive of mild volume loss. No focal consolidation, pleural effusion or pneumothorax is present. There are no acute osseous abnormalities.
